  "scenarioDescription": "\n  <ul class=\"exoplanets-navigation-menu\">\n  <li><button href=\"#system\">System</button>\n  <li><button href=\"#LHS 3844\">Star</button>\n  <li><button href=\"#LHS 3844-b\">b</button></li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1 id=\"system\">The LHS 3844 Exoplanetary System</h1>\n  <p>The LHS 3844 system contains 1 exoplanet. It is located 48.55 light years away from the solar system.</p>\n    <div class=\"celestial-object-wrapper\" id=\"LHS 3844\">\n  <section>\n  <h2>Star</h2>\n  <div class=\"size-comparison-wrapper\">\n  <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 100px; height: 100px; background-color: rgb(255, 242.3979365143785, 230.54885609599933);\">\n    <label>Sun</label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 19px; height: 19px; background-color: rgb(255, 178.38680965925045, 112.38839013816022)\">\n<label>LHS 3844</label>\n</div>\n</div>\n  </section>\n  <table cellspacing=\"0\">\n  <tr>\n    <td>Mass</td>\n    <td>0.15 solar masses</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Radius</td>\n    <td>0.19 solar radiae</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Temperature</td>\n    <td>3036 kelvin</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Stellar Metallicity</td>\n    <td>- decimal exponent</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Age</td>\n    <td>- billion years</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n     \n    <div class=\"celestial-object-wrapper\" id=\"LHS 3844-b\">\n      <section>\n        <h2>LHS 3844-b</h2>\n        <p> At 2.251 Earth masses, LHS 3844 b is a so called Super Earth. Super Earths could be terrestrial worlds like Earth, but they could also be ocean worlds or terrestrial worlds wrapped in a substantial atmosphere, in which case some refer to them as Mini Neptunes.     </p>\n        <div class=\"size-comparison-wrapper\">\n          <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 10px; height: 10px;\">\n            <label>Earth</label>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"celestial-sphere\" style=\"width: 13.03px; height: 13.03px;\">\n            <label>LHS 3844-b</label>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <table cellspacing=\"0\">\n          <tr>\n            <td>Mass</td>\n            <td>2.250 Earth masses</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Density</td>\n            <td>5.590 grams per cubic centimeter</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Radius</td>\n            <td>1.303 Earth radiae</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Semi-major Axis</td>\n            <td>0.00622 AU</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Eccentricity</td>\n            <td>NaN</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Orbital Period</td>\n            <td>0.463 days</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Discovery Method</td>\n            <td>Transit</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Discovery Facility</td>\n            <td>Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS)</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Discovery Telescope</td>\n            <td>0.1 m TESS Telescope</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Discovery Instrument</td>\n            <td>TESS CCD Array</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Discovery Date</td>\n            <td>2019-02</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Reference</td>\n            <td><a refstr=VANDERSPEK_ET_AL__2019 href=https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2019ApJ...871L..24V/abstract target=ref>Vanderspek et al. 2019</a></td>\n          </tr>\n        </table>\n      </section>\n    </div></a>\n  ",
